]]\n[[Category:2001 in film]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the 1968 science-fiction film, novel, and related items|2001: A Space Odyssey}}\n{{Year nav topic5|2001|film|home video|television}}\n{{Yearsinfilm}}\n\nThe year '''2001 in film''' involved some significant events, including the first installments of the ''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' series, ''[[The Fast and the Furious]]'' and ''[[Shrek (franchise)|Shrek]]'' franchises, and ''[[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|The Lord of the Rings]]'' and ''[[Ocean's (film series)|Ocean's]]'' trilogies. Significant non-English language films released included ''[[Monsoon Wedding]]'', ''[[Am\u00e9lie]]'' and ''[[Spirited Away]]''.\n\n==Highest-grossing films==\nThe top 10 films released in 2001 by worldwide gross are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/year/world/2001/?ref_=bo_cso_table_1|title=2001 Worldwide Box Office |website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\"\n|+ Highest-grossing films of 2001\n|-\n! Rank!! Title !! Distributor !! Worldwide gross\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| ''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film)|Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone]]''\n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| $975,755,371\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring]]''\n| [[New Line Cinema|New Line]]\n| $871,530,324\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n| ''[[Monsters, Inc.]]''\n| [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Disney]]\n| $525,366,597<ref>{{cite web|title=Monsters, Inc. (2001) |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=main&id=monstersinc.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120629132627/https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=main&id=monstersinc.htm |archivedate=29 June 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n| ''[[Shrek]]''\n| [[DreamWorks Pictures|DreamWorks]]\n| $484,409,218\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| ''[[Ocean's Eleven]]''\n| Warner Bros.\n| $450,717,150\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| ''[[Pearl Harbor (film)|Pearl Harbor]]''\n| Disney\n| $449,220,945\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| ''[[The Mummy Returns]]''\n| rowspan=2| [[Universal Pictures|Universal]]\n| $433,013,274\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| ''[[Jurassic Park III]]''\n| $368,780,809\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9\n| ''[[Planet of the Apes (2001 film)|Planet of the Apes]]''\n| [[Twentieth Century Fox Film Corporation|20th Century Fox]]\n| $362,211,740\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| ''[[Hannibal (2001 film)|Hannibal]]''\n| [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Studios Inc.|Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Studios]]\n| $351,692,268\n|}\n\n''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film)|Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone]]'' has grossed $974.7 million; it was the highest-grossing film in the [[Harry Potter (film series)|''Harry Potter'']] film franchise until ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2]]'' surpassed it in [[2011 in film|2011]].\n\n''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film)|Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone]]'' and ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring]]'' both grossed more than $800 million, marking the first time that two films released in the same year grossed more than $800 million at the box office.\n\n==Events==\n* June 22 \u2013 ''[[The Fast and the Furious (2001 film)|The Fast and the Furious]]'' is released, launching [[The Fast and the Furious|one]] of the [[List of highest-grossing films#Highest-grossing franchises and film series|highest-grossing franchises]] in film history.\n* August 8 \u2013 Actors [[Tom Cruise]] and [[Nicole Kidman]] divorce.\n* November 2 \u2013 ''[[Monsters, Inc.]]'' opens with the best ticket sales ever for an [[animated film]] and the 6th best of all time.\n* November 16 and December 19 \u2013 The beginning of two acclaimed film series based on best-selling novels: ''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' and ''[[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|The Lord of the Rings]]'', respectively.\n\n===Award ceremonies===\n* [[6th Empire Awards]]\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20px;\"| Category/Organization !! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"| [[7th Critics' Choice Awards]]<br /> January 11, 2002 !! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"| [[59th Golden Globe Awards]]<br />January 20, 2002 !! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"| [[55th British Academy Film Awards|55th BAFTA Awards]]<br />February 24, 2002 !! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"|[[Producers Guild of America Awards 2001|Producers]], [[54th Directors Guild of America Awards|Directors]], [[8th Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors]], and [[Writers Guild of America Awards 2001|Writers Guild Awards]]!! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:250px;\"| [[74th Academy Awards]]<br /> March 24, 2002\n|-\n! width=200| Drama !! style=\"width:200px;\"| Musical or Comedy\n|-\n| Best Film || colspan=\"2\"| ''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]'' || ''[[Moulin Rouge!]]'' || ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring]]'' ||''[[Moulin Rouge!]]''|| ''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]''\n|-\n| Best Director || [[Ron Howard]]<br/>''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]''<br/>[[Baz Luhrmann]]<br/>''[[Moulin Rouge!]]'' || colspan=\"2\"| [[Robert Altman]]<br/>''[[Gosford Park]]'' || [[Peter Jackson]]<br/>''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring]]'' ||colspan=2| [[Ron Howard]]<br/>''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]''\n|-\n| Best Actor || colspan=\"2\"| [[Russell Crowe]]<br/>''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]'' || [[Gene Hackman]]<br/>''[[The Royal Tenenbaums]]'' || colspan=\"2\"| [[Russell Crowe]]<br/>''[[A Beautiful Mind (film)|A Beautiful Mind]]'' || [[Denzel Washington]]<br/>''[[Training Day]]'' \n|-\n| Be